Package dashboard.control

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AuxArrowPad
    Implements an auxiliary arrow pad for controlling a vehicle.
    AuxArrowPad.Builder
    Builder for the AuxArrowPad class.
    BufferReadoutControl
    Implements a controller for the BufferReadout class.
    BufferReadoutControl.Builder
    Builder for the BufferReadoutControl class.
    Button
    Provides the base functionality for a rectangular button with which the user can interact.
    ButtonGrid
    Provides the base functionality for a grid of Buttons.
    ButtonGrid.Builder<T extends ButtonGrid.Builder>
    Builder for the ButtonGrid class, to be extended by all subclasses of ButtonGrid.
    Control
    Provides the base functionality for all user-interactable widgets that require mouse input.
    CustomButtonGrid
    Implements a custom grid of Buttons that can be constructed at runtime.
    CustomButtonGrid.Builder
    Builder for the CustomButtonGrid class.
    CustomGroup
    Implements a custom group of widgets that can be constructed at runtime.
    CustomGroup.Builder
    Builder for the CustomGroup class.
    Group
    Provides the base functionality for a container widget that can hold other widgets.
    Group.Builder<T extends Group.Builder>
    Builder for the Group class, to be extended by all subclasses of Group.
    HoldButton
    Implements a Button that if held, repeatedly executes its onAction until it is released.
    MainArrowPad
    Implements a main arrow pad for controlling a vehicle.
    MainArrowPad.Builder
    Builder for the MainArrowPad class.
    MultiIncrementer
    Implements a controller for multiple Incrementables.
    MultiIncrementer.Builder
    Builder for the MultiIncrementer class.
    SingleIncrementer
    Implements a controller for a single Incrementable.
    SingleIncrementer.Builder
    Builder for the SingleIncrementer class.
    ToggleButton
    Implements a Button that behaves like a switch or flip-flop.
    TouchButton
    Implements a Button that executes its onAction exactly once when pressed, and its offAction exactly once when released.
